  "What is the image of (3, −4) after a 90° counterclockwise rotation about the origin?": "",
  "Substitute the input value into the function expression and simplify using order of operations. The result is (4, 3). The other options — '(−3, 4)', '(−4, −3)', and '(3, 4)' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": "",
  "What is the coordinate rule for a 180° rotation about the origin?": "",
  "A rotation turns a figure around a fixed point by a given angle. 90° rotations: (x,y) → (-y,x). 180°: (x,y) → (-x,-y). The answer is (x, y) → (−x, −y). The other options — '(x, y) → (−y, x)', '(x, y) → (y, −x)', and '(x, y) → (x, −y)' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": "",
  "What is the image of (−1, 6) after a 270° counterclockwise rotation about the origin?": "",
